        {
          "id": "action_hs-tr-s1_3",
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Each candlestick shows four data points: Open, High, Low, and Close. The body is the range between open and close. Wicks show the highest and lowest prices touched during the period. Green candles closed higher — buyers won. Red candles closed lower — sellers won.",
          "audioUrl": "/audio/lessons/oc-hs-trading/0-3.mp3"
        },
        {
          "id": "action_hs-tr-s1_4",
          "type": "spotlight",
          "elementId": "hs-tr-s1-c1-t"
        },
        {
          "id": "action_hs-tr-s1_5",
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Bullish Engulfing: a large green candle completely engulfs the previous red candle. Buyers overwhelmed sellers. A strong reversal signal at the bottom of a downtrend.",
          "audioUrl": "/audio/lessons/oc-hs-trading/0-5.mp3"
        },
        {
          "id": "action_hs-tr-s1_6",
          "type": "spotlight",
          "elementId": "hs-tr-s1-c2-t"
        },
        {
          "id": "action_hs-tr-s1_7",
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Doji: open and close are almost identical — tiny body, long wicks. Buyers and sellers are equally matched. The market is undecided. Usually precedes a big move in either direction — wait for confirmation.",
          "audioUrl": "/audio/lessons/oc-hs-trading/0-7.mp3"
        },
        {
          "id": "action_hs-tr-s1_8",
          "type": "spotlight",
          "elementId": "hs-tr-s1-c3-t"
        },
        {
          "id": "action_hs-tr-s1_9",
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Shooting Star: long upper wick, small body at the bottom. Price rallied hard but was rejected — sellers pushed it back down. A bearish reversal signal after an uptrend.",
          "audioUrl": "/audio/lessons/oc-hs-trading/0-9.mp3"
        },
        {
          "id": "action_hs-tr-s1_10",
          "type": "spotlight",
          "elementId": "hs-tr-s1-sr-b"
        },
        {
          "id": "action_hs-tr-s1_11",
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Support is a price zone where buying has historically stopped declines. The more times it's tested and held, the stronger it is. Resistance is a zone where selling has historically capped rallies. Breaking through resistance convincingly is a bullish signal. And role reversal: old resistance becomes new support after a breakout — one of the most reliable patterns in technical analysis.",
          "audioUrl": "/audio/lessons/oc-hs-trading/0-11.mp3"
        },
        {
          "id": "action_hs-tr-s1_12",
          "type": "spotlight",
          "elementId": "hs-tr-s1-insight-t"
        },
        {
          "id": "action_hs-tr-s1_13",
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Key rule: No single candle gives a complete picture. Context matters — where is this candle forming? At support? After a trend? Candlesticks are clues, not certainties. Always confirm with volume and other signals.",
          "audioUrl": "/audio/lessons/oc-hs-trading/0-13.mp3"
        }
      ]
