        {
          "id": "action_hs-tr-s2_3",
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "RSI measures overbought and oversold conditions on a zero to one hundred scale using a 14-period lookback. RSI above 70 signals overbought — potential pullback ahead. RSI below 30 signals oversold — potential bounce. RSI at 50 is neutral. Important caveat: in strong trends, RSI can stay extreme for extended periods. Don't short just because RSI hits 70.",
          "audioUrl": "/audio/lessons/oc-hs-trading/1-3.mp3"
        },
