          "id": "action_hs-tr-s2_5",
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "MACD tracks the difference between the 12-period and 26-period exponential moving averages. A signal line is the 9-period EMA of the MACD itself. Bullish cross: MACD crosses above the signal line — buy signal. Bearish cross: MACD crosses below — sell signal. Divergence: price makes a new high but MACD doesn't — momentum is weakening, watch out.",
          "audioUrl": "/audio/lessons/oc-hs-trading/1-5.mp3"
        },
        {
          "id": "action_hs-tr-s2_6",
          "type": "spotlight",
          "elementId": "hs-tr-s2-orders-b"
        },
        {
          "id": "action_hs-tr-s2_7",
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Order types: Market orders execute immediately at the best available price — guaranteed fill. Limit orders only fill at your specified price or better — not guaranteed. Stop-loss orders auto-exit your position if price falls to your set level — this defines your maximum loss before you enter. Take-profit orders lock in gains automatically at your target. And always know your risk-reward ratio — risk one hundred dollars to make two hundred gives you a 1 to 2 ratio. Professionals target minimum 1 to 2.",
          "audioUrl": "/audio/lessons/oc-hs-trading/1-7.mp3"
        },
        {
          "id": "action_hs-tr-s2_8",
          "type": "spotlight",
          "elementId": "hs-tr-s2-psych-b"
        },
        {
          "id": "action_hs-tr-s2_9",
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Studies show 70 to 80 percent of retail traders lose money — not from lack of indicators, but from psychology. FOMO: chasing coins after they're already up fifty percent. Loss aversion: holding losers hoping they come back, turning small losses into account-wrecking drawdowns. Overtrading: forced entries with no edge. Revenge trading: doubling down after a loss to recover — this is how accounts blow up. Copy trading bypasses all of this by following disciplined traders automatically.",
          "audioUrl": "/audio/lessons/oc-hs-trading/1-9.mp3"
        }
      ]
    },
