            "analysis": "FOMO (Fear of Missing Out) is the emotional impulse to buy a coin after it's already rallied sharply. You buy because you're afraid of missing further gains — but you often end up buying the top while smart money is already taking profits. FOMO entries are one of the most common causes of retail losses.",
